A man has been arrested on suspicion of arson after a huge explosion at a home in Yorkshire left a gaping hole in the terraced property and caused a fire in the roof. Residents living near to the house in Goole were evacuated in the early hours of the morning and the street remains closed.    "It's the first time I've seen something like this. The intervention of the firemen and the police was exceptional. "Their involvement in our safety is commendable, not being English citizens, the neighbours welcomed us into their homes. It was a cold night and a lesson from which I learned. "Everyone be careful. From 1am to 9 am we were evacuated - a terrible experience so please take care of you and your homes."     Investigations as to the cause of the fire and the explosion are ongoing. In a statement Humberside Police said: "We are in attendance at the scene of a suspected gas explosion at a house on Malborough Road in Goole. "We were called at 1.10am today (Sunday 22 January) to reports of an explosion and fire at the address. "The area was cordoned off to allow emergency services to work safely and for the safety of the public. "No one is reported to have been seriously injured. A man has been arrested at the scene on suspicion of committing arson with intent to endanger life. "He has been taken into police custody. Neighbouring properties have been evacuated as a precaution. Occupants of all neighbouring properties have been accounted for. "A road closure and police cordon remain in place, and we are asking for people to stay away from the area whilst emergency services deal with the incident."      We'll be bringing you the very latest updates, pictures and video on this breaking news story. For the latest news and breaking news visit: /news Stay up to date with all the big headlines, pictures, analysis, opinion and video on the stories that matter to you. Follow our social media accounts here on facebook.com/DailyExpress and @daily_express 